			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am not in favor of increasing the experience for those that group over those that solo.  Group members do not have as high a risk factor when hunting and should not be rewarded for the lack of risk!  I have found thus far that any class can solo if you hunt wisely and in the proper places.  Hunting solo does get harder the higher you go and you can be limited to places that do not give the great loot.  Why should a solo player be penilized any further?  Groups are able to hunt in places that they would not be able to survive alone and they have less down time, why should they get more experience for that?  Besides, some players have limited play time and can not spend most of looking for a group only to have to log off as soon as it gets going good.  I think it is fairly balanced as it is!  Do not punish the solo player!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
